Description.LocalizedString: She’d found the kerchief blowing in the wind on a tree branch. A rare blessing during a difficult life.
A dress that was already tattered when it was stolen. The breast has been ripped away to make room for Victor.
A sickle with a massive nail penetrating the steel. The addition has little to do with practicality and everything to do with cruelty.

Any sense of repulsion vanishes when you’re on death’s door.
She had never felt so soothed by warmth, as she huddled in the pigsty, soaking in blood.
A cleaver soaked by the insides of a recently butchered pig.
A crown emanating a festive and ominous aura created by The Entity’s biggest fan.

A crown crafted for a very special anniversary.
“Thank you for supporting & inspiring us along the years!” —The Dead by Daylight Team
Her hair caught debris of ropes and waste as she swam through oily waves, attempting to fish for survival.
The fisherman's clothes that she adapted to allow her brother to swim and breathe safely.
She gutted each fish with her dirty nails and used rusted hooks to catch more.
Charlotte gazed upon a ship at sea and imagined stealing the clothes of a naval officer and sailing West to this New World.
The journey would be dangerous, and difficult, but at its end, a land where sweet syrup poured from the trees.
One day, these awful weapons could be used not for violence, but to build a new place for them to call home.
This scythe, hidden away for weeks with a stock of candy, ended up covered in foul larvae.
Nature provides the best weapons.
The bones clutched to her flesh, and the moss invaded her extremities.
White flowers bloomed on her hidden side.
